{4014}{}{is still a part of their brain sensible to the mind of}
{4015}{}{humans. Alas, this tele-cortex only responds to the}
{4016}{}{Master's mind. I am certain, however, that it can be}
{4017}{}{adapted to any human's mind using a process called}
{4018}{}{neural reorganization. Once I succeed, I shall have}
{4019}{}{thousands of absolutely loyal soldiers. With the Unity}
{4020}{}{resurrected I can conquer the entire world!}
{4021}{}{**END-PAR**}
{4022}{}{[650913]}
{4023}{}{Be damned, world! One of the centaurs died today,}
{4024}{}{suddenly, without warning. During post-mortem I}
{4025}{}{discovered that Forced Evolutionary Virus used as}
{4026}{}{primary neurotransformer mutated heavily since the last}
{4027}{}{test, and ceased to serve its original purpose. I must}
{4028}{}{redo the virus transmutation procedure, regardless of}
{4029}{}{the delay.}
{4030}{}{The autopsy, however, indicated that I am on the right}
{4031}{}{track. The neural organizer worked the way it was}
{4032}{}{supposed to in the beginning, altering the tele-cortext}
{4033}{}{structure properly. After a couple of minutes the FEV}
{4034}{}{became unstable, attacking the somatic tissue which,}
{4035}{}{unfortunately, led to exitus. Obviously, the mutation}
{4036}{}{must be regulated somehow, as it is currently too}
{4037}{}{excessive.}
{4038}{}{**END-PAR**}
{4039}{}{[680315]}
{4040}{}{Experimenting with neural reorganization using an}
{4041}{}{altered FEV batch 13-024 yields positive results with}
{4042}{}{both floaters and centaurs. The modern plague virus}
{4043}{}{proved to be a good mutation regulator. Good fortune}
{4044}{}{smiles on me. Proof that I was always meant to rule}
{4045}{}{这个世界!}
{4046}{}{Floaters seem to be more exploitable than centaurs.}
{4047}{}{Probably because they have fewer heads. Three young}
{4048}{}{floaters are being altered from infancy. They are}
{4049}{}{showing great progress. My hopes lie with them. They}
{4050}{}{shall become my very first soldiers!}
{4051}{}{**END-PAR**}
{4052}{}{[691224]}
{4053}{}{I can feel my ultimate goal is at hand. Sometimes I}
{4054}{}{speculate why was I predestined to be the next great}
{4055}{}{leader of the world. I understand now where the Master}
{4056}{}{erred. He held down too much, not using all the}
{4057}{}{available resources. Blinded by his utopic visions of}
{4058}{}{harmony, he failed to see that the proper way to}
{4059}{}{establish power only lays through massive violence. He}
{4060}{}{refused to use it sufficiently. The entire Unity was}
{4061}{}{smothered in his utopic dreams. It was always meant to}
{4062}{}{fall. The Master held back. I shall not repeat his}
{4063}{}{mistakes. More and more, I become aware of how misled}
{4064}{}{he and his entire organization were. Perhaps I should}
{4065}{}{have disposed of my robe, my only connection with}
{4066}{}{Children of the Cathedral, but I became accustomed to}
{4067}{}{it over the years. Besides, it seems to have a calming}
{4068}{}{effect on floaters and centaurs. That could, however,}
{4069}{}{imply that their knowledge comes from genetic memory.}
{4070}{}{Nonsense! I should keep myself away from such foolish}
{4071}{}{thoughts, I still have a lot to accomplish. It is time}
{4072}{}{to embrace my fate.}
{4073}{}{**END-PAR**}
{4074}{}{[700330]}
{4075}{}{Today I performed the last set of tests on three young}
{4076}{}{floaters. Subject 1 shows the most positive reaction to}
{4077}{}{the transmutation agent. I think it's ready for the}
{4078}{}{final phase. It shall be treated with the final dose of}
{4079}{}{the neuromutation virus today. Then it shall prove its}
{4080}{}{allegiance to me. It shall lead its brethren and bring}
{4081}{}{the nearest city to oblivion!}
{4082}{}{The new dawn of humanity shall end before it even}
{4083}{}{started! People shall submit to my tremendous power -}
{4084}{}{or die.}
{4085}{}{**END-DISK**}

{5000}{}{October 23, 2077}
{5001}{}{They really did it... It was looming over us the whole}
{5002}{}{time, I was prepared for it, but I still can't believe}
{5003}{}{the world really ended. Thank God the alarm was sounded}
{5004}{}{in time. We managed to hide in our bunker built exactly}
{5005}{}{for that purpose. We're safe. Many people didn't take}
{5006}{}{the alarm seriously. They thought it was just another}
{5007}{}{exercise. Most of the others went to hide in vaults.}
{5008}{}{How long can they be safe there? Safe in a vault, built}
{5009}{}{and controlled by the Government, the same Government,}
{5010}{}{which started a war and launched all of their nuclear}
{5011}{}{weapons! They can't be trusted. They won't have any}
{5012}{}{problem with turning the vault dwellers into their}
{5013}{}{slaves. Or riots may break out, and everyone will be at}
{5014}{}{each other's throats. I'd rather take care of my family}
{5015}{}{on my own, that's my responsibility. That's why I built}
{5016}{}{this bunker below our house. It's for me, my wife, and}
{5017}{}{our son Donald. Judith didn't really agree with it, but}
{5018}{}{she must understand that this is the best solution. I'm}
{5019}{}{sure she'll realize that in time. I think she's just in}
{5020}{}{shock because of what happened. I mean, who wouldn't}
{5021}{}{be? She keeps talking about my brother who has a spot}
{5022}{}{in Vault 16. But he doesn't have a family that he needs}
{5023}{}{to take care of, and he's young. He doesn't understand}
{5024}{}{what responsibility is yet. God, I hope he's alright.}
{5025}{}{**END-PAR**}
{5026}{}{October 30, 2077}
{5027}{}{A week has passed and we're all still feeling a bit}
{5028}{}{dazed. Me and Judith often go through the whole day}
{5029}{}{without talking, her merely dropping a venomous remark}
{5030}{}{from time to time. Something about living in an}
{5031}{}{accursed hole underground. It will take a while before}
{5032}{}{she accepts the terrible fact that we're going to be}
{5033}{}{stuck here for many years. I know that, but she's}
{5034}{}{starting to get on my nerves. And Donald is constantly}
{5035}{}{asking stupid questions. He's just six years old, he}
{5036}{}{doesn't understand what's going on.}
{5037}{}{**END-PAR**}
{5038}{}{November 15, 2077}
{5039}{}{We're slowly settling in and getting used to our}
{5040}{}{situation. My wife is finally talking to me. I just}
{5041}{}{wish our conversations didn't end in arguments so}
{5042}{}{often. When she started whining about how awful our}
{5043}{}{bunker is again, I got so angry I shouted at her to get}
{5044}{}{out and die if she doesn't like it. I'm ashamed I let}
{5045}{}{myself be provoked this way. Donald overheard. It's}
{5046}{}{hard enough for him to keep listening to his own mother}
{5047}{}{complaining all the time, and now this.}
{5048}{}{**END-PAR**}
{5049}{}{December 4, 2077}
{5050}{}{While I was checking our supplies today, I found out}
{5051}{}{that half of our tin cans are rotten. They're}
{5052}{}{completely inedible, we could get food poisoning from}
{5053}{}{them. I'm certain that I stored them properly, and}
{5054}{}{according to the expiration dates, they should've}
{5055}{}{lasted for several more decades. Some bastards probably}
{5056}{}{got rich on selling expired tin cans, all they needed}
{5057}{}{to do was change the labels. Well, it's not like I can}
{5058}{}{file a complaint anywhere now. We'll have to save our}
{5059}{}{food even more to make sure that what we have lasts}
{5060}{}{longer. Judith just added this to her repertoire of}
{5061}{}{criticisms.}
{5062}{}{**END-PAR**}
{5063}{}{December 7, 2077}
{5064}{}{Yesterday, Judith quite bluntly said that she'd be}
{5065}{}{better off if she went to the vault with my brother. I}
{5066}{}{couldn't restrain myself and slapped her. She hasn't}
{5067}{}{talked to me for the rest of the day. Judith's hostile}
{5068}{}{silence was perhaps worse than her venomous talk. But}
{5069}{}{it's hard enough for me to think about my brother. I}
{5070}{}{keep telling myself I should've tried harder to}
{5071}{}{convince him to join us. Perhaps I could've broken his}
{5072}{}{stubbornness. Sure, our little shelter isn't ideal, but}
{5073}{}{it can't be worse than a vault. Hard to say what}
{5074}{}{horrors are taking place there right now.}
{5075}{}{**END-PAR**}
{5076}{}{December 11, 2077}
{5077}{}{I've done a terrible thing. Judith started complaining}
{5078}{}{again this morning, we had a big argument and I just}
{5079}{}{couldn't take it. I took my pistol and hit her in the}
{5080}{}{head with it. Again, and again. I just couldn't stop, I}
{5081}{}{kept hearing her criticisms even after she was long}
{5082}{}{silent, her face beaten to a bloody pulp. She said it}
{5083}{}{would've been better if we all died right after the}
{5084}{}{bombs fell instead of living in this grave. Why did she}
{5085}{}{have to say something like that? Why did she have to}
{5086}{}{say she wanted us all to be dead? I don't even know why}
{5087}{}{I had a gun hidden right next to the bed. Luckily,}
{5088}{}{Donald wasn't in the room at the time. He doesn't know}
{5089}{}{what happened.}
{5090}{}{**END-PAR**}
{5091}{}{December 13, 2077}
{5092}{}{Donald keeps asking about his mom. I made something up,}
{5093}{}{but he just keeps asking on. I wasn't even able to}
{5094}{}{respond to him today. I had to stay alone so he}
{5095}{}{wouldn't see me cry. God, what have I done? I've killed}
{5096}{}{the boy's mother, my own wife!}
{5097}{}{**END-PAR**}
{5098}{}{December 18, 2077}
{5099}{}{Since this morning, I've had the feeling that I smell}
{5100}{}{something strange. Perhaps the smell of burning, but}
{5101}{}{it's barely perceptible. Maybe I'm just telling that to}
{5102}{}{myself because I don't believe anything good could}
{5103}{}{happen to us ever again. If it really is a}
{5104}{}{short-circuit, there's a danger of fire on the}
{5105}{}{electrical wiring. We could suffocate on the smoke}
{5106}{}{here. I'll have to check all the cables I can get to.}
{5107}{}{Maybe I'll stop thinking of Judith so much during work,}
{5108}{}{I still see her bloody face before my eyes. May the God}
{5109}{}{forgive me.}
{5110}{}{**END-PAR**}
{5111}{}{December 19, 2077}
{5112}{}{The smell is more noticeable than yesterday. I've}
{5113}{}{discovered what the problem is. It's worse than a}
{5114}{}{short-circuit. The air filters aren't working properly,}
{5115}{}{the dust from the outside keeps getting in. With every}
{5116}{}{breath we take increasing doses of radiation. I don't}
{5117}{}{know how to repair that. I've tried nearly everything,}
{5118}{}{I don't know what I'm going to do.}
{5119}{}{**END-PAR**}
{5120}{}{December 21, 2077}
{5121}{}{I have to end this. It's pointless. We'd just slowly}
{5122}{}{die of radiation exposure. I can't do that to Donald.}
{5123}{}{We'll have a big dinner this evening then I'll end it.}
{5124}{}{Donald is being a good boy. He's in a good mood because}
{5125}{}{I told him he'll see his mother soon. I think that}
{5126}{}{knowing it will all end soon, I finally feel relieved.}
{5127}{}{**END-DISK**}

