{7000}{}{What exactly is a mutant? Some say that it is a}
{7001}{}{physically changed human. But they are WRONG! A mutant}
{7002}{}{may have been human once, but once he changes, he}
{7003}{}{loses all his humanity - and that's why he must die!}
{7004}{}{Even if the physical manifestations of mutation are}
{7005}{}{minimal. On the contrary, such a mutant is even more}
{7006}{}{dangerous, and must be ELIMINATED!}
{7007}{}{**END-PAR**}
{7008}{}{Have the mutants ever created anything of value? NO!}
{7009}{}{What did they ever accomplish? Nothing but murder and}
{7010}{}{destruction! Only fools dare say that we should}
{7011}{}{negotiate with mutants. It is NONSENSE! The mutant}
{7012}{}{minds are so changed that no discussion can be had with}
{7013}{}{them. They are aggressive and violent! They understand}
{7014}{}{nothing else, and can't be dealt with in any other way!}
{7015}{}{We must be stronger than them, and exterminate them}
{7016}{}{all! Before they do the same to us.}
{7017}{}{**END-PAR**}
{7018}{}{How could there be any doubt, when their existence}
{7019}{}{itself is the greatest proof? For if a mutant was}
{7020}{}{capable of reason he would surely kill himself! He}
{7021}{}{would understand how hopeless and pointless his}
{7022}{}{existence is, and would put an end to his torment! But}
{7023}{}{instead, they fight against us humans, so we'll have to}
{7024}{}{take them out ourselves. We must exterminate every last}
{7025}{}{one of them!}
{7026}{}{**END-PAR**}
{7027}{}{Mutants don't hesitate to use every opportunity they}
{7028}{}{have to kill humans, and that is why we cannot afford}
{7029}{}{any doubt, and must eradicate them ALL!}
{7030}{}{**END-PAR**}
{7031}{}{We must not miss the slightest mutation, because it}
{7032}{}{would spread to other pure humans, and from them to}
{7033}{}{others... A world without humans, filled with}
{7034}{}{senseless, violent mutants - that's the future we are}
{7035}{}{trying to prevent! That is why EVERY SINGLE MUTANT}
{7036}{}{MUST DIE!}
{7037}{}{**END-PAR**}
{7038}{}{That's what every one of you here is fighting for, and}
{7039}{}{you should feel proud of that. As I am proud of you!}
{7040}{}{Because you're saving humanity! Because you're saving}
{7041}{}{THE WORLD! But we mustn't rejoice yet, we mustn't}
{7042}{}{relent... Until the mutants have been WIPED FROM THE}
{7043}{}{FACE OF THE EARTH!}
{7044}{}{**END-DISK**}

{8000}{}{Foreword}
{8001}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8002}{}{Our organization, the Mutant Hunters, grows with every}
{8003}{}{passing day, and this gives me the conviction that we}
{8004}{}{will one day reach our common goal - the salvation of}
{8005}{}{pure humans from mutants. When that blessed time}
{8006}{}{comes, however, it will be necessary to remember what}
{8007}{}{preceded so that the people who fought for the safety}
{8008}{}{of others, and everything they had to sacrifice, is not}
{8009}{}{forgotten. It should also serve as a warning that this}
{8010}{}{must not happen again, so that mutants and mutations}
{8011}{}{may never threaten the lives of pure humans ever again.}
{8012}{}{That's why I wrote this history of the Hunters, which}
{8013}{}{may also be the only thing left after us should the}
{8014}{}{last Mutant Hunter fall. If that happens, let this}
{8015}{}{document be a moral support for those that would follow}
{8016}{}{in our steps. Let them know there were people before}
{8017}{}{them that were determined to fight against the mutants,}
{8018}{}{so they may learn from the mistakes which may have led}
{8019}{}{to our demise.}
{8020}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8021}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8022}{}{                                               Sebastian}
{8023}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8024}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8025}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8026}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8027}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8028}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8029}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8030}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8031}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8032}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8033}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8034}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8035}{}{I saw the mutants ravaging this already desolate land,}
{8036}{}{I saw the super mutants killing, torturing and}
{8037}{}{capturing people. I saw pure humans mating with}
{8038}{}{mutants, I saw the hideous monsters that come from}
{8039}{}{such unions, sometimes living no longer than a few}
{8040}{}{hours. It made me sick. I saw that decline of humanity,}
{8041}{}{I saw it rushing to its destruction, and decided to do}
{8042}{}{something about it.}
{8043}{}{There were always enough groups of pure humans strong}
{8044}{}{enough to survive, but their lives were without}
{8045}{}{meaning, without purpose. They were merely surviving,}
{8046}{}{and their existence meant nothing on its own. But when}
{8047}{}{I showed them what I'd seen, they understood me, and}
{8048}{}{saw the danger threatening all pure humans on their}
{8049}{}{own. They joined me, and I united them with a promise}
{8050}{}{that we'll rid the world of mutants - a promise that I}
{8051}{}{hope we'll one day fulfill.}
{8052}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8053}{}{We helped villages and towns, ridding them of the foul}
{8054}{}{mutants, despite the nonsensical resistance of the}
{8055}{}{local people. But above all, we grew stronger. Not only}
{8056}{}{were we joined by more and more pure humans willing to}
{8057}{}{fight, we also searched for forgotten pre-war weapons}
{8058}{}{and armor that would helps us in our fight. This was}
{8059}{}{necessary because units created by the mad Master with}
{8060}{}{the help of the betrayers of the human race, the}
{8061}{}{Children of the Cathedral, were already spreading}
{8062}{}{across the wasteland. We fought the super mutants many}
{8063}{}{times. We killed many of them, but many brave Hunters}
{8064}{}{died as well.}
{8065}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8066}{}{Thanks to our efforts, the super mutants stopped}
{8067}{}{appearing in our territory and remained far in the}
{8068}{}{west. But then a new menace appeared - the Rebirth.}
{8069}{}{The Rebirth is some new religion that spread amongst}
{8070}{}{the ghouls, and they, armed with the best weapons}
{8071}{}{people had created before the war, started to pillage}
{8072}{}{towns and villages. We don't know where they got such}
{8073}{}{equipment, or anything about their foolish faith. The}
{8074}{}{ghouls talk only of someone called Savior, no doubt}
{8075}{}{another disgusting mutant. Not only do they kill in his}
{8076}{}{name, they also capture pure humans and take them}
{8077}{}{away, but we don't know where or why.}
{8078}{}{So we continued to look for pre-war technology, as well}
{8079}{}{as new allies. We found both in the only city that}
{8080}{}{resisted the Rebirth in the area. Or at least we}
{8081}{}{thought so. We came to Albuquerque, the city that had}
{8082}{}{already endured a large ghoul attack, and offer our}
{8083}{}{help and an alliance. But we were refused, offered only}
{8084}{}{a twisted agreement concluded in 2157. In return for}
{8085}{}{defending Albuquerque against the invaders, we were}
{8086}{}{allowed to eradicate the threat within the city! They}
{8087}{}{"graciously" gave us the permission to purge the city}
{8088}{}{of mutants, when it should've been their natural duty}
{8089}{}{as pure humans! And all we received was the minimum}
{8090}{}{material required for the construction of our base.}
{8091}{}{People of the empire, blinded by their easy lives,}
{8092}{}{didn't realize what threat the Rebirth really was. And}
{8093}{}{not only the Rebirth, but all mutants.}
{8094}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8095}{}{In 2160, many dwellers paid for their foolishness with}
{8096}{}{their lives. The ghouls mustered enough strength for a}
{8097}{}{second large attack on the city. Without tactics or}
{8098}{}{reason, they ferociously threw themselves at}
{8099}{}{Albuquerque. Their better weapons and especially their}
{8100}{}{numerical superiority allowed them to penetrate deep}
{8101}{}{into the city. While confusion spread amongst the}
{8102}{}{imperial soldiers, we Mutant Hunters eventually forced}
{8103}{}{the ghouls to retreat. But not even after our triumph}
{8104}{}{did the emperor offer us the technology and equipment}
{8105}{}{that they have amply available. The only thing he}
{8106}{}{agreed with was the construction of a wall around the}
{8107}{}{entire city. There was plenty of material available.}
{8108}{}{Not only from around the city, but especially from the}
{8109}{}{ruins that remained after the ghoul invasion. That}
{8110}{}{destroyed part of the city has been called the Dead}
{8111}{}{Quarter ever since.}
{8112}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8113}{}{Our relentless search across the wasteland finally bore}
{8114}{}{fruit in 2161. We discovered an old army warehouse, and}
{8115}{}{turned it into our second base. Thanks to its excellent}
{8116}{}{location, it remains hidden from the Rebirth patrols}
{8117}{}{that frequently appear in the area. Thus, we don't have}
{8118}{}{to take the captured ghouls far, and especially not}
{8119}{}{into a city that we strive to keep clean from mutants.}
{8120}{}{That's why the base, headed by commander Tunrida, is}
{8121}{}{mostly use for interrogations and conducting tests on}
{8122}{}{the mutants.}
{8123}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8124}{}{In 2166, we finally took at least a part of what}
{8125}{}{rightfully belongs to us. We defend Albuquerque from}
{8126}{}{mutants both inside and outside, and the empire still}
{8127}{}{refuses to help us. We defend their lives, as well as}
{8128}{}{the lives of all pure humans, and they refuse to give}
{8129}{}{us the technology that would be of incredible help not}
{8130}{}{only in our fight against the Rebirth, but all the}
{8131}{}{mutants! That's why we took the third floor of their}
{8132}{}{Vault by force. We used killers genetically engineered}
{8133}{}{by pre-war scientists to capture the floor without the}
{8134}{}{empire suspecting a thing. The emperor responded to the}
{8135}{}{loss of the two floors of their Vault by shutting the}
{8136}{}{Imperial City off from the rest of Albuquerque, proving}
{8137}{}{that there was no one capable of sensible leadership}
{8138}{}{among the descendants of the Vault 16 dwellers.}
{8139}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8140}{}{Update December 9, 2169:}
{8141}{}{**END-PAR**}
{8142}{}{A few days earlier, we received a message from Tunrida}
{8143}{}{saying that they've finally managed to break one of the}
{8144}{}{Rebirth ghouls during interrogation, and gain new}
{8145}{}{information. She was apparently close to discovering}
{8146}{}{the location of their base. However, the base has not}
{8147}{}{responded to any of our calls since then. Until a group}
{8148}{}{of our scouts discovered that it was occupied by super}
{8149}{}{mutants. The foul beasts killed every Hunter stationed}
{8150}{}{in the base, and it can be assumed that they destroyed}
{8151}{}{everything there.}
{8152}{}{**END-DISK**}

{9000}{}{We fight not for glory, but for the salvation of}
{9001}{}{mankind. However, the names and deeds of the great}
{9002}{}{warriors who lost their lives fighting the mutants}
{9003}{}{should not be forgotten.}
{9004}{}{**END-PAR**}
{9005}{}{Cole Gassko}
{9006}{}{Mercilessly kept purging Albuquerque of mutants hiding}
{9007}{}{in the city. He was killed by one of those he so}
{9008}{}{dutifully protected - a city dweller.}
{9009}{}{**END-PAR**}
{9010}{}{Leena}
{9011}{}{Her unit was ambushed by a group of Rebirth ghouls. She}
{9012}{}{was the only one to survive, and she chased the ghouls,}
{9013}{}{even through irradiated areas, until she killed them}
{9014}{}{all. She died a few days later due to radiation}
{9015}{}{poisoning.}
{9016}{}{**END-PAR**}
{9017}{}{Bastel "the Merciless"}
{9018}{}{Led the Hunters during the cleansing of many towns and}
{9019}{}{villages from mutants. He fell during the second large}
{9020}{}{attack on Albuquerque.}
{9021}{}{**END-PAR**}
{9022}{}{Andrew Ryamon}
{9023}{}{Together with the Hunters under his command, he killed}
{9024}{}{many of the Master's super mutants, until they were}
{9025}{}{treacherously ambushed by a large group of them. He was}
{9026}{}{killed along with the majority of his troops.}
{9027}{}{**END-PAR**}
{9028}{}{"Mad" Sam}
{9029}{}{A great fighter and slayer of mutants. Killed along}
{9030}{}{with other Hunters by the first alien queen after she}
{9031}{}{awakened.}
{9032}{}{**END-PAR**}
{9033}{}{**END-PAR**}
{9034}{}{**END-PAR**}
{9035}{}{Soram}
{9036}{}{Killed many mutants, defended Albuquerque during the}
{9037}{}{second large attack and took part in the construction}
{9038}{}{of the city wall. When he found out that his body was}
{9039}{}{showing the signs of mutation, he correctly chose to}
{9040}{}{shoot}
{9041}{}{himself.}
{9042}{}{**END-PAR**}
{9043}{}{Anna Taylor}
{9044}{}{Lured a patrol of the Master's super mutants to}
{9045}{}{herself, and killed them all by detonating a powerful}
{9046}{}{explosive charge strapped to her body.}
{9047}{}{**END-PAR**}
{9048}{}{Vukovich}
{9049}{}{Valiantly fought against the Rebirth ghouls during the}
{9050}{}{second large attack on Albuquerque. Died after}
{9051}{}{sustaining extensive injuries.}
{9052}{}{**END-DISK**}

{10000}{}{The subject is a non-humanoid creature moving on two}
{10001}{}{rear limbs. The front appendages are very flexible and}
{10002}{}{transformed into a kind of tentacles. On the apical end}
{10003}{}{of the oval, cylindrical body is a large mouth with a}
{10004}{}{row of large teeth. Cloaca is placed distally. The tail}
{10005}{}{is missing. The head part of the body has two round}
{10006}{}{protrusions covered by skin - likely its photosensoric}
{10007}{}{organs. There are no signs of other sensory organs.}
{10008}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10009}{}{The epidermis is gray, very tough, and composed of}
{10010}{}{three layers. In addition to the sweat glands, it}
{10011}{}{contains a number of special glands, whose function is}
{10012}{}{unknown. Subcutaneous tissue is not particularly rich}
{10013}{}{in fat.}
{10014}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10015}{}{Musculature is of is a very unusual character. The}
{10016}{}{nearest equivalent would probably be found in human}
{10017}{}{cardiac muscle. This type of muscular tissue is very}
{10018}{}{dependent on flawless supply of blood, on the other}
{10019}{}{hand, it allows tasks that require great strength for}
{10020}{}{extended periods of time. The aliens would make for}
{10021}{}{great marathon runners, but the structure of their}
{10022}{}{limbs does not match that.}
{10023}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10024}{}{The respiratory system is similar to that of birds, in}
{10025}{}{addition to two lung lobes, it also contains rear lung}
{10026}{}{bags, however, they are stunted and likely are not used}
{10027}{}{in an environment rich in oxygen. The lung area}
{10028}{}{bloodstream leads into a system of endocrine glands}
{10029}{}{secreting unusual chemicals. It seems that these}
{10030}{}{complex organic substances are capable of neutralizing}
{10031}{}{several kinds of toxins that may be present in the air,}
{10032}{}{primarily chlorine-based compounds.}
{10033}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10034}{}{The digestive system consists of two stomachs, a}
{10035}{}{muscular and a glandular one, which are connected to an}
{10036}{}{extensive lobed duodenum, which reaches highly unusual}
{10037}{}{dimensions - about 120% of the stomach. Judging by}
{10038}{}{remnants of undigested food found in the lobes, this}
{10039}{}{organ is used to store food for times when there is}
{10040}{}{nothing to hunt, similarly to Arachnidae.}
{10041}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10042}{}{The nervous system is tubular, the same as in}
{10043}{}{vertebrates. The brain is made up of two half-globes}
{10044}{}{that are relatively large (weight 900 g), but have only}
{10045}{}{very few creases. Telencephalon is stunted, however,}
{10046}{}{with the exception of one frontal lobe, which is}
{10047}{}{unusually large. The function of this section is not}
{10048}{}{entirely clear yet, however, we found a very strong}
{10049}{}{link with the subcortical centers that are used for}
{10050}{}{detection of shapes in humans, and with the center}
{10051}{}{responsible for fighting and hunting.}
{10052}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10053}{}{The cellular structure is ordinary, with slightly}
{10054}{}{increased amount of mitochondria. The only unusual}
{10055}{}{thing is the diffused core with minimal amount of}
{10056}{}{sensitive matter, which makes it very resistant to hard}
{10057}{}{radiation. The core also contains an unusually low}
{10058}{}{amount of chromatin, far less than even the lowest of}
{10059}{}{the animals. This has to do with the shocking}
{10060}{}{discoveries in the field of genetics.}
{10061}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10062}{}{Microbiochemical analysis:}
{10063}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10064}{}{From the viewpoint of genetics, the alien completely}
{10065}{}{surpasses everything we know. Its hereditary}
{10066}{}{information is stored in what might be called the penta}
{10067}{}{alpha helix - a helix made of five primary strips of}
{10068}{}{its own ribonucleic acid. This DNA is supplemented by a}
{10069}{}{quantity of completely unknown proteins. The histones}
{10070}{}{keeping the whole structure together are extremely}
{10071}{}{complex and yet stable. The molecular structure is}
{10072}{}{simply amazing. The diffused cores contain five pairs}
{10073}{}{of chromosomes, which are relatively short and make the}
{10074}{}{same sense when read from either side. This creates a}
{10075}{}{sort of secondary failsafe, so the chances of fatal}
{10076}{}{damage to the code is eight times less than in normal}
{10077}{}{organisms. We haven't found any parasitic DNA during}
{10078}{}{sequencing, unless we count long stretches coding the}
{10079}{}{transcription of various enzymes, however, the alien}
{10080}{}{does not use these under normal conditions. We assume}
{10081}{}{that these grecipesh allow aliens to adapt to a}
{10082}{}{variety of external conditions extremely quickly. After}
{10083}{}{being brought into a foreign environment, these}
{10084}{}{creatures can fully adapt within a single generation.}
{10085}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10086}{}{All of this confirms my original assumption that aliens}
{10087}{}{are not a natural species modified by breeding and}
{10088}{}{selection, and certainly are not mutants that occurred}
{10089}{}{naturally. This is a creature created completely from}
{10090}{}{scratch. An artificial organism. An organic machine.}
{10091}{}{For what purpose was it created?}
{10092}{}{The answer to the question can be found by observing}
{10093}{}{the captured aliens. They are willing and able to}
{10094}{}{attack anything that disrupts their territory. During}
{10095}{}{experiments with a deathclaw in the open terrarium, the}
{10096}{}{deathclaw was victorious, but when he proceeded further}
{10097}{}{into the alien lair, it was torn to pieces. The aliens}
{10098}{}{are able to perfectly coordinate their moves, even}
{10099}{}{though we did not detect any usual forms of}
{10100}{}{communication among them. Although they can perfectly}
{10101}{}{orientate themselves in both light and dark, they seem}
{10102}{}{to prefer darkness, apparently to help cool their}
{10103}{}{oversized organism. However, they don't seem to mind}
{10104}{}{heat at all! The overall structure of their bodies}
{10105}{}{makes them almost perfect killers. What is missing to}
{10106}{}{complete perfection is caused by the concessions needed}
{10107}{}{to ensure reproduction. The aliens are gonochoric. The}
{10108}{}{mother, also called the Queen, is larger than the}
{10109}{}{males. The Queen, after mating with one of the males,}
{10110}{}{lays a large number of eggs. The Queen can keep viable}
{10111}{}{sperm in special pockets and maintain them for a very}
{10112}{}{long period of time, this way she can lay fertilized}
{10113}{}{eggs long after seeing the last male. The sex of the}
{10114}{}{offspring isn't genetically determined, but further}
{10115}{}{details are not yet known.}
{10116}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10117}{}{It is likely that the aliens were created before the}
{10118}{}{War as killing machines for the army. They've more than}
{10119}{}{proven themselves in that role, even in these times,}
{10120}{}{however, we do not currently recommend their use. The}
{10121}{}{pre-war scientists managed to build into them only one}
{10122}{}{control mechanism, a so called "genetic clock". As we}
{10123}{}{have already stated, the alien's genome is grouped in}
{10124}{}{ten chromosomes. That is not entirely accurate, as}
{10125}{}{there is one extra (non-paired!) short chromosome. Due}
{10126}{}{to the influence of hormones contained in the male}
{10127}{}{sexual secretions, there is an expression of genes on}
{10128}{}{this otherwise non-functioning chromosome after mating.}
{10129}{}{Though this only happens in the primordial gonocytes of}
{10130}{}{the embryonic tissue, it happens in all of them at}
{10131}{}{once! These chemical reactions are not yet fully}
{10132}{}{clarified. The microchromosome is composed of three}
{10133}{}{parts: The first (in front of the centriola) creates}
{10134}{}{depended RNA polymerase, which than cuts off a small}
{10135}{}{(but always the same sized) part of the chromatin on}
{10136}{}{the opposite end of the microchromosome. The third part}
{10137}{}{of the microchromosome is firmly connected to the}
{10138}{}{second part, but unlike it, it is nonsensical. The}
{10139}{}{order of the bases has no purpose and renders the code}
{10140}{}{in the second, middle section of microchromosome}
{10141}{}{inactive. However, during each division, a part of this}
{10142}{}{meaningless section is cut off until there is none}
{10143}{}{left, causing the second part to become active and}
{10144}{}{immediately begin its expression. Its result is}
{10145}{}{cellular death. This means that after a set (hard-wired}
{10146}{}{in advance!) number of divisions (followed by the}
{10147}{}{creation of eggs), all the cells of the embryonal line}
{10148}{}{commit mass suicide and the queen becomes sterile. The}
{10149}{}{old world scientists probably did this because they}
{10150}{}{thought it would ensure that the aliens wouldn't breed}
{10151}{}{uncontrollably in case of an escape. I consider this}
{10152}{}{failsafe to be extremely effective, though theories}
{10153}{}{have appeared that tried to prove it's potential}
{10154}{}{inefficacy under extreme conditions, but the hypotheses}
{10155}{}{were found to be improbable.}
{10156}{}{There are no other apparent means of controlling the}
{10157}{}{aliens. Training them is impossible at the current}
{10158}{}{state of our knowledge. They're like an unguided}
{10159}{}{nuclear missile, you release them and who knows where}
{10160}{}{they'll fall. However, there were indications that}
{10161}{}{pointed to the possibility of changing that fact. It}
{10162}{}{seems very likely that in the future, after more}
{10163}{}{advanced research is done, we will be able to}
{10164}{}{understand the structure of the alien brains and use}
{10165}{}{this knowledge to control them. Though it will require}
{10166}{}{long and arduous effort from the entire science team,}
{10167}{}{we belief that it will be a success.}
{10168}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10169}{}{Signed: Science team 1}
{10170}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10171}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10172}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10173}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10174}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10175}{}{Reconnaissance team report (selected passages):}
{10176}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10177}{}{The second reconnaissance team discovered a large}
{10178}{}{complex of cryochambers on the third underground floor.}
{10179}{}{Five of them were active, but three seemed to have met}
{10180}{}{a fatal accident in the past - there was only some}
{10181}{}{sticky biological crap inside. The other two chambers}
{10182}{}{contained unknown organisms. Some idiot from the team}
{10183}{}{triggered the unfreezing program on one of them,}
{10184}{}{reviving the organism inside. According to the first}
{10185}{}{reports, it just waddled around in confusion and tried}
{10186}{}{to orientate itself, but a moment after we heard only}
{10187}{}{screams and gunfire.}
{10188}{}{The foreign organism clearly proved its vitality. It}
{10189}{}{massacred the entire first team, as well as the second}
{10190}{}{one I dispatched. When I arrived with more people, all}
{10191}{}{eight Hunters were dead, mostly torn into pieces. We}
{10192}{}{lost the creature, it likely escaped into the wasteland}
{10193}{}{using the ventilation system.}
{10194}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10195}{}{I've called all squads to the unfreezing of the second}
{10196}{}{organism and oversaw the process personally. As with}
{10197}{}{the previous case, it was a queen of the species that}
{10198}{}{someone idiotically named aliens. As the queen started}
{10199}{}{to regain her life functions, we pumped a large amount}
{10200}{}{of tranquilizers into her, so she didn't fully react,}
{10201}{}{however, she still managed to kill one man that wasn't}
{10202}{}{careful enough. We securely tied her with several}
{10203}{}{chains and placed her into a transport container, in}
{10204}{}{which we managed to get her into our base without a}
{10205}{}{fuss.}
{10206}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10207}{}{There wasn't anything else of use in the military base}
{10208}{}{we discovered, except various large scientific devices,}
{10209}{}{most of them non-functional. However, since the base is}
{10210}{}{too far, it wouldn't be worth it to disassemble them}
{10211}{}{and transport them to Albuquerque. That's why I had}
{10212}{}{the base destroyed using the local stock of industrial}
{10213}{}{explosives. The underground floors were systematically}
{10214}{}{buried and the surface floors were blown up.}
{10215}{}{**END-PAR**}
{10216}{}{Signed: Commander Tunrida}
{10217}{}{**END-DISK**}

{11000}{}{Report from the forward base 4Q 2169}
{11001}{}{Tunrida, commander of the forward base}
{11002}{}{**END-PAR**}
{11003}{}{10/31/2169}
{11004}{}{Mild Rebirth activity in our area, which began in}
{11005}{}{February of this year, still persists. Once again we}
{11006}{}{came across several units heading towards the north}
{11007}{}{and northwest. The ghouls are after something, but}
{11008}{}{whatever it is, it's not in this area.}
{11009}{}{**END-PAR**}
{11010}{}{11/9/2169}
{11011}{}{We have completed the last batch of doctor Yaotzin's}
{11012}{}{tests on our test subjects. I will attach a second}
{11013}{}{holodisk with the results. We do not have anymore test}
{11014}{}{subjects right now. Although I have to thank Yaotzin}
{11015}{}{for the excellent show I got from the reactions the}
{11016}{}{mutants had to his substance, it is not suited to}
{11017}{}{practical application because it took them too long to}
{11018}{}{die.}
{11019}{}{**END-PAR**}
{11020}{}{11/27/2169}
{11021}{}{The scouts have caught a lone Rebirth ghoul in the}
{11022}{}{wastes. Due to previous failures in gathering}
{11023}{}{information, I'm going to take care of his tomorrow}
{11024}{}{interrogation personally.}
{11025}{}{**END-PAR**}
{11026}{}{11/28/2169}
{11027}{}{After four hours and 22 minutes of interrogation, the}
{11028}{}{ghoul finally started talking. He gave us a lot of}
{11029}{}{important and serious information. The Rebirth has a}
{11030}{}{base in a Vault-Tec research complex, which contains a}
{11031}{}{machine capable of regenerating tissue, and which is}
{11032}{}{thus able to transform even a ghoul into a pure human.}
{11033}{}{However, this procedure requires donors from among the}
{11034}{}{genetically pure humans. This is the reason for the}
{11035}{}{Rebirth raids on human towns and villages. It sounds}
{11036}{}{ridiculous, but it is the truth. I made sure that the}
{11037}{}{ghoul would not be able to lie to us.}
{11038}{}{Of course, mutants cannot really become truly pure}
{11039}{}{humans, not even such advanced pre-war technology can}
{11040}{}{do the impossible. The transformation is only}
{11041}{}{temporary, after some time (depending on the genetic}
{11042}{}{purity of the donors), the organism collapses and the}
{11043}{}{body literally falls apart. But the Rebirth is led by a}
{11044}{}{madman called the Savior. He let himself be transformed}
{11045}{}{as the first and is keeping a large part of the Rebirth}
{11046}{}{in the belief that the machine works as imagined, and a}
{11047}{}{smaller, more informed part, in the belief that the}
{11048}{}{machine is malfunctioning and they must find out how to}
{11049}{}{repair it. And for that, all the ghouls are willing to}
{11050}{}{fight for him. The interrogated ghoul was not able to}
{11051}{}{tell us the numbers of the Rebirth ghouls, but he}
{11052}{}{confirmed that they keep increasing, as evidenced by}
{11053}{}{our observations.}
{11054}{}{For now they only transform one mutant a year, thus,}
{11055}{}{pure humans die mainly as a result of heinous}
{11056}{}{experiments meant to help fix the machine. The last}
{11057}{}{transformed mutant, the Thirteenth Reborn, as they}
{11058}{}{themselves call him, discovered part of the truth and}
{11059}{}{managed to escape. That's the reason for the increased}
{11060}{}{activity of the Rebirth in the north, as they are}
{11061}{}{looking for him. His capture would certainly be useful}
{11062}{}{to us. However, he looks like a normal, pure human. He}
{11063}{}{is only recognizable by his vault jumpsuit with the}
{11064}{}{number 13 on it, signifying the order of his}
{11065}{}{transformation, unless he got rid of it. It is also}
{11066}{}{possible that he already died as a consequence of the}
{11067}{}{transformation.}
{11068}{}{However, it is more important to attack the base of the}
{11069}{}{Rebirth as soon as possible to stop their atrocities.}
{11070}{}{I've managed to gain not only its location, but also}
{11071}{}{information concerning how to get inside without a}
{11072}{}{fight. The security measures are weak, the mutants}
{11073}{}{could not handle anything difficult. It is enough to}
{11074}{}{mask one's appearance, for example by wearing a robe or}
{11075}{}{a suit of power armor, and use the password "New Life"}
{11076}{}{and show their talisman to identify oneself.}
{11077}{}{**END-PAR**}
{11078}{}{Coordinates for the Rebirth base:}
{11079}{}{[Location recorded into map]}
{11080}{}{**END-PAR**}
{11081}{}{Given the importance of these findings, I'm sending a}
{11082}{}{group with my report to Albuquerque tomorrow instead}
{11083}{}{of the usual date. The main base was informed of our}
{11084}{}{success during the interrogation by radio.}
{11085}{}{**END-PAR**}
{11086}{}{11/29/2169}
{11087}{}{Sending the report will have to wait. Our scouts have}
{11088}{}{discovered a group of supermutants heading to our}
{11089}{}{position. We will need every last man, and I also don't}
{11090}{}{want the report to fall into their hands by accident.}
{11091}{}{As soon as we take care of the supermutants, I will}
{11092}{}{head to Albuquerque with the report personally.}
{11093}{}{**END-PAR**}
{11094}{}{12/1/2169}
{11095}{}{One of my men, Colin, tried to run away to avoid the}
{11096}{}{battle. I shot him.}
{11097}{}{The supermutants will attack soon. They're not}
{11098}{}{intelligent enough for any tactics besides simply}
{11099}{}{throwing themselves at us, we will handle them easily.}
{11100}{}{**END-DISK**}

