{13000}{}{Since the first attacks of the Rebirth, our forces have}
{13001}{}{faced a hostile army equipped with highly resistant}
{13002}{}{armor, including powered infantry armor (model T-51b).}
{13003}{}{This raises the need to increase the effectiveness of}
{13004}{}{our weapons against these advanced protective}
{13005}{}{measures. One of the possible directions is the}
{13006}{}{development of pulse weapons, thus, we began to}
{13007}{}{examine the issue of development and production of}
{13008}{}{these high-energy systems. Analysis of the YK32 pistol,}
{13009}{}{of which we've had several pieces in our armory since}
{13010}{}{the war, has served as the basis for this research.}
{13011}{}{**END-PAR**}
{13012}{}{The pulse weapon from the Yuma Flats Energy Consortium}
{13013}{}{is characterized by solid construction and high}
{13014}{}{performance. It is quite notable for its unique}
{13015}{}{cigar-like shape and three distinct cooling ribs. The}
{13016}{}{gun fits very well into the hand, as the pistol grip,}
{13017}{}{where the batteries are hidden, is considerably heavier}
{13018}{}{than the rest of the weapon, which basically only}
{13019}{}{consists of light electronics hidden in chassis made of}
{13020}{}{non-magnetic metals. The electronics in this pistol are}
{13021}{}{made with amazing precision. Secondary and tertiary}
{13022}{}{converters are characterized by an unusually high}
{13023}{}{efficiency, and the primary energy circuits of the}
{13024}{}{weapons are also designed in original, efficient style}
{13025}{}{- after all, this gun has only three cooling ribs. The}
{13026}{}{residual heat generated by a system of particle}
{13027}{}{accelerators is very small and the weapon does not}
{13028}{}{appear to have the tendency to overheat even after}
{13029}{}{many consecutive shots. However, the downside of this}
{13030}{}{performance is lower accuracy. The gun has only one}
{13031}{}{radiation rectifier battery. It was simply not possible}
{13032}{}{to fit more of them into the weapon. When firing from a}
{13033}{}{greater distance, the pistol thus suffers from a}
{13034}{}{considerable dispersion. Along the same line, it also}
{13035}{}{suffers from a problem, or rather is the victim of the}
{13036}{}{overall design, which is inadequate capacity,}
{13037}{}{sufficient for just five shots.}
{13038}{}{**END-PAR**}
{13039}{}{Despite the novel solution of the model YK32 structure,}
{13040}{}{it's obvious that it's not possible to concentrate all}
{13041}{}{the necessary systems (i.e. pulse field generators,}
{13042}{}{radiation rectifiers, cooling systems, feedback}
{13043}{}{eliminators, power accumulators) into a small}
{13044}{}{one-handed weapon that would be simple to operate but}
{13045}{}{would be of sufficient combat value to us. Low range}
{13046}{}{and small energy capacity seem to be the critical}
{13047}{}{factors. The pulse weapon itself needs to be designed}
{13048}{}{from the beginning as a large two-handed rifle of}
{13049}{}{generous design, one that is able to contain everything}
{13050}{}{that needs to be there. This will make it possible to}
{13051}{}{significantly increase the efficiency of the weapon.}
{13052}{}{**END-PAR**}
{13053}{}{As for the structural elements, it is worth trying to}
{13054}{}{emulate the design of the YK32 primary circuits. The}
{13055}{}{particle generators can be taken over without problems,}
{13056}{}{and thinking of something better may not even be}
{13057}{}{possible. The original diagnostic and regulatory}
{13058}{}{mechanisms are also suitable. However, the feedback}
{13059}{}{elimination systems will be more complicated. Adapting}
{13060}{}{the systems from the pistol to the higher power of the}
{13061}{}{rifle may be problematic, on the other hand, the higher}
{13062}{}{mass of the body of the weapon will be very helpful}
{13063}{}{here. As for the accumulator, charging, and}
{13064}{}{transformation systems, it will be best to adapt them}
{13065}{}{from the creations of the Winchester company, as they}
{13066}{}{are more massive and can handle higher energy values}
{13067}{}{than the delicate Yuma Flats accumulators. We will have}
{13068}{}{to develop the targeting electronics (which the YK32}
{13069}{}{completely lacks) ourselves, or stick with the system}
{13070}{}{developed near the end of the war by Wattz Electronics.}
{13071}{}{The development of our own targeting system will of}
{13072}{}{course take several months. On the other hand, the}
{13073}{}{Watzz Electronics system may not be fully compatible}
{13074}{}{with the rectifiers and the generators of the pulse}
{13075}{}{field. It will be necessary to carry out a more}
{13076}{}{thorough research in this regard.}
{13077}{}{**END-PAR**}
{13078}{}{The development of the pulse rifle will no doubt take a}
{13079}{}{long time, and its manufacture will require a}
{13080}{}{significant amount of resources. However, the empire}
{13081}{}{already possesses the necessary materials. If we choose}
{13082}{}{to go in the direction of pulse technology, the}
{13083}{}{resulting weapon could be superior to all other}
{13084}{}{personal weapons both from the purely technological}
{13085}{}{side and for its tactical combat value.}
{13086}{}{**END-PAR**}
{13087}{}{**END-PAR**}
{13088}{}{Attachments:}
{13089}{}{**END-PAR**}
{13090}{}{Complete design plans of the YK32 pulse pistol.}
{13091}{}{**END-DISK**}

{14000}{}{In the period after the opening of the vault and the}
{14001}{}{subsequent resettlement of the surface, our military}
{14002}{}{encountered numerous hostile groups. Our trained and}
{14003}{}{disciplined soldiers handled every tribal and raider}
{14004}{}{attack, as well as attacks by mutated animals. However,}
{14005}{}{in order to ensure greater security and to unify the}
{14006}{}{representative look of the imperial army, the}
{14007}{}{development of a new, unified element of personal}
{14008}{}{defense began.}
{14009}{}{**END-PAR**}
{14010}{}{The basic requirements that shaped our ideas were high}
{14011}{}{resistance to explosions and fired projectiles, low}
{14012}{}{production costs and the possibility of serial}
{14013}{}{production in large quantities. The concept of a system}
{14014}{}{of anatomically shaped metal plates worn over one's}
{14015}{}{clothes appeared ideal for this. Such armor had to be}
{14016}{}{designed to avoid impeding the movement of the wearer}
{14017}{}{while still offering maximum protection.}
{14018}{}{**END-PAR**}
{14019}{}{For the creation of the corpus, a quarter inch of}
{14020}{}{high-quality boiler steel was used, reinforced with an}
{14021}{}{additional welded layer on the chest and back. Flexible}
{14022}{}{components are made of fifty layers of kevlar fibers,}
{14023}{}{and clamping elements are made up of strong brahmin}
{14024}{}{leather. The inner lining of the the armor is made up}
{14025}{}{of ten layers of nomex. The armor is welded, the moving}
{14026}{}{metal components are connected with screws, and the}
{14027}{}{fabric and leather are riveted to the metal.}
{14028}{}{**END-PAR**}
{14029}{}{Practical tests have shown that the armor provides}
{14030}{}{complete protection for the chest, shoulders and back}
{14031}{}{against both stabbing and cutting attacks. The new}
{14032}{}{armor also seems highly effective against the commonly}
{14033}{}{used soft-core ammunition. The kevlar parts are of}
{14034}{}{course ineffective against piercing ammo shot from}
{14035}{}{shorter range. The imperial soldiers are trained to}
{14036}{}{fully understand this limitation. The option of}
{14037}{}{multiplying the layer of fibers was rejected due to}
{14038}{}{limited supplies of pre-war materials. In the case of}
{14039}{}{deploying the armor against military weapons using}
{14040}{}{armor-piercing ammunition, the survival of the wearer}
{14041}{}{cannot be guaranteed. But weapons of this kind are}
{14042}{}{quite rare in the wasteland.}
{14043}{}{**END-PAR**}
{14044}{}{Using nomex and kevlar fibers for the construction of}
{14045}{}{the lining and stomach protection proved to be an}
{14046}{}{excellent decision during the tests. Fabric made from}
{14047}{}{the combination of these fibers gives the armor a}
{14048}{}{phenomenal resistance to explosions incomparable to}
{14049}{}{regular metal armor. Even in the case of exposure to}
{14050}{}{the effects of relatively powerful explosives during}
{14051}{}{testing, the volunteers only complained about losing}
{14052}{}{their breath. Besides the resistance of the pre-war}
{14053}{}{fabrics against explosions and shrapnel, we must also}
{14054}{}{mention their excellent resistance against fire. The}
{14055}{}{armor as a whole is capable of resisting exposure to}
{14056}{}{temperatures of up to 600 degrees Fahrenheit.}
{14057}{}{**END-PAR**}
{14058}{}{The metal armor with nomex-kevlar fiber has proven}
{14059}{}{itself to be a suitable armor for the imperial army. It}
{14060}{}{has saved the lives of many heroic soldiers. Each man}
{14061}{}{or woman in active service is assigned a suit of it.}
{14062}{}{Due to the excellent results and so far sufficient}
{14063}{}{stocks of material, it will stay in production for at}
{14064}{}{least a few more years.}
{14065}{}{**END-DISK**}

{15000}{}{Vault-Tec Biological Research Complex - New Mexico}
{15001}{}{**END-PAR**}
{15002}{}{To satisfy the growing research potential of Vault-Tec,}
{15003}{}{in 2047 we began the construction of a six floor}
{15004}{}{complex in New Mexico, and its construction was}
{15005}{}{finished four years later. All current research and}
{15006}{}{development on biology and other related fields was}
{15007}{}{moved here, but we also started new projects for which}
{15008}{}{we did not have capacity before.}
{15009}{}{The project with the highest priority was creating an}
{15010}{}{effective treatment for radiation exposure and}
{15011}{}{mutation, as another possible stage in rebuilding}
{15012}{}{civilization after a possible nuclear war. Thus began}
{15013}{}{the most demanding project in the history of the}
{15014}{}{company, surpassing in complexity even the successful}
{15015}{}{GECK project. There is no doubt that it will take many}
{15016}{}{more years, and will require much effort before the}
{15017}{}{project reaches the planned result.}
{15018}{}{A department for manufacturing basic Vault equipment}
{15019}{}{(such as jumpsuits and Pip-Boys) was also built in the}
{15020}{}{complex, as its convenient geographical location}
{15021}{}{permits the easily distribution of goods to vaults in}
{15022}{}{the west and south of the USA.}
{15023}{}{Three years of smooth operation have shown that the}
{15024}{}{facility has enough free space and capacity. Part of}
{15025}{}{the capacity was freed up by finishing some of the}
{15026}{}{smaller projects. This made it possible to begin}
{15027}{}{developing weapons in close cooperation with the United}
{15028}{}{States' Army. Considering the nature of the local}
{15029}{}{research, it mostly concerned biological and chemical}
{15030}{}{weapons.}
{15031}{}{**END-PAR**}
{15032}{}{The complex is completely self-sufficient, just like a}
{15033}{}{vault, and in the extreme case of a nuclear attack, it}
{15034}{}{can be closed in the same way. The unique underground}
{15035}{}{structure ensures it can withstand even a direct hit}
{15036}{}{from a tactical nuclear missile. The main power source}
{15037}{}{is a massive nuclear reactor near the bottom of the}
{15038}{}{complex, on the sixth floor. This cutting-edge reactor}
{15039}{}{guarantees smooth operation for several decades.}
{15040}{}{Besides modern technologies and lab equipment, the}
{15041}{}{employees can make use of a spacious cafeteria with a}
{15042}{}{wide selection of food, as well as luxurious resting}
{15043}{}{rooms. In the infirmary, the highly qualified staff}
{15044}{}{have cutting-edge equipment at their disposal, allowing}
{15045}{}{them to perform even the most demanding procedures.}
{15046}{}{**END-PAR**}
{15047}{}{The computers are connected to a local network, TecNet}
{15048}{}{version 4.1, controlled by the main computer that is}
{15049}{}{completely satisfactory even though it is not equipped}
{15050}{}{with artificial intelligence, as Vault-Tec has no}
{15051}{}{confidence in the reliability of AIs. The latest}
{15052}{}{version of the software ensures quick and seamless}
{15053}{}{communication. Advanced safety protocols prevent all}
{15054}{}{sorts of attacks and allow the system to raise the}
{15055}{}{alarm and immediately locate unauthorized actions made}
{15056}{}{by users. All terminals are also equipped with a}
{15057}{}{modern, in-built microwave connector, which allows them}
{15058}{}{to wirelessly communicate with Pip-Boys, even with the}
{15059}{}{oldest version - 2000.}
{15060}{}{**END-PAR**}
{15061}{}{Security is provided by Vault-Tec personnel, as well as}
{15062}{}{US Army soldiers complemented by modern security}
{15063}{}{robots equipped with deadly weapons. The robots are}
{15064}{}{connected with the security components of TecNet,}
{15065}{}{meaning authorized personnel are able to set detailed}
{15066}{}{defensive parameters. The robots are also completely}
{15067}{}{self-sufficient, and, on a fully charged battery, will}
{15068}{}{continue to operate for up to 10 days.}
{15069}{}{**END-PAR**}
{15070}{}{Warning!}
{15071}{}{10/23/2077 at 13:42, the main computer received a}
{15072}{}{verified signal with the command to immediately close}
{15073}{}{the complex as per security protocol 16. The main}
{15074}{}{entrance was immediately sealed.}
{15075}{}{At 13:43, nerve gas BX-8 was released.}
{15076}{}{At 13:48, there were no signs of life detected.}
{15077}{}{At 13:50 the last particles of the BX-8 gas dispersed.}
{15078}{}{The sealing of the complex has been successful.}
{15079}{}{**END-DISK**}

{16000}{}{Full report:}
{16001}{}{**END-PAR**}
{16002}{}{The advanced healing medication designated super}
{16003}{}{stimpak has proven to be invaluable in combat}
{16004}{}{situations where powerful and rapid treatment is}
{16005}{}{required. However, its negative side-effects,}
{16006}{}{manifesting mere minutes after being administered, were}
{16007}{}{responsible for permanent organ damage and, in some}
{16008}{}{cases, even the death of many soldiers. For these}
{16009}{}{reasons, we have received a contract from the United}
{16010}{}{States Armed Forces for a medication with greater}
{16011}{}{healing power which retains none of these inopportune}
{16012}{}{characteristics. This new medication has been named}
{16013}{}{ultra stimpak.}
{16014}{}{**END-PAR**}
{16015}{}{An increase in healing potency was easily accomplished}
{16016}{}{by increasing the volume of alpha-fibrinogen and}
{16017}{}{hydroxyproline contained in each dose. As expected,}
{16018}{}{testing confirmed that these ratios are hazardous to}
{16019}{}{humans, with a single dose proving sufficient to}
{16020}{}{provoke a cardiac arrest in susceptible individuals. As}
{16021}{}{a result, our laboratories began developing a mixture}
{16022}{}{of suppressors and calcium ion emitters which, when}
{16023}{}{combined with basic proteins, should mitigate the ultra}
{16024}{}{stimpak's undesirable side-effects without impacting}
{16025}{}{its healing ability. Batch 5-003 managed to reduce the}
{16026}{}{potency of the side-effects, while 5-018 blocked them}
{16027}{}{completely. However, more thorough testing later}
{16028}{}{revealed that ultra stimpak's effective service life}
{16029}{}{was limited to two or three weeks at most. After that}
{16030}{}{time, chemical decomposition occurs, weakening the}
{16031}{}{effect of molecular markers. Tropocollagen structures}
{16032}{}{then manifest, as in batch 5-003, or lead to the}
{16033}{}{collapse of control mechanisms with fatal consequences}
{16034}{}{- as seen with the super stimpak. Further development}
{16035}{}{was consequently focused on the stricter control of}
{16036}{}{glycoprotein distribution, especially using synthetic}
{16037}{}{fullerene-based nanocapsules. Research in this area has}
{16038}{}{progressed our understanding of macromolecules}
{16039}{}{considerably. When the lab produced batch 9-012, it}
{16040}{}{felt more like a by-product than an end-goal. The}
{16041}{}{results of our research will change the future of}
{16042}{}{pharmacology. Batch 9-012 resembles a perfect,}
{16043}{}{subcellular clockwork mechanism. It can quickly heal}
{16044}{}{even severe injuries, yet possesses none of the}
{16045}{}{negative side-effects of our previous efforts. The}
{16046}{}{overall lifetime of the macromolecules used is}
{16047}{}{estimated to be 120 years - which should prove more}
{16048}{}{than sufficient.}
{16049}{}{**END-PAR**}
{16050}{}{At present, we have already begun mass producing ultra}
{16051}{}{stimpaks. We should be able to supply all elite and}
{16052}{}{special units of the United States Armed Forces during}
{16053}{}{the year 2077, and all other military branches within}
{16054}{}{the next two or three years. We estimate that ultra}
{16055}{}{stimpaks shall completely replace super stimpaks within}
{16056}{}{the military during the next four years.}
{16057}{}{**END-DISK**}

