{17140}{}{machine and everything even remotely related to it.}
{17141}{}{When they finally came here, I acted surprised as if I}
{17142}{}{hadn't known about them right from the start. I told}
{17143}{}{them I'd used the machine, but when I tested it}
{17144}{}{afterwards, I found out there was something wrong with}
{17145}{}{it. They were so taken aback that their dream, a}
{17146}{}{rebirth machine, as I named it, truly exists, that they}
{17147}{}{accepted everything I told them.}
{17148}{}{**END-PAR**}
{17149}{}{11/30/2150}
{17150}{}{It only took me a few days to become their leader. To}
{17151}{}{them I'm the savior who'll lead them to a rebirth for}
{17152}{}{all. It's strange that these creatures who will be the}
{17153}{}{instrument of my mission, must know absolutely nothing}
{17154}{}{of its nature in order to reach the final goal. They}
{17155}{}{are so determined to become normal humans once again}
{17156}{}{that nothing will stop them until they've accomplished}
{17157}{}{it. But that's impossible, so they'll keep going at it}
{17158}{}{until the very end. The end of all mankind. Maybe then,}
{17159}{}{once they're alone, they'll realize they stand on the}
{17160}{}{brink of extermination which must be carried out to}
{17161}{}{alleviate the world of all the remnants of human}
{17162}{}{existence.}
{17163}{}{As their savior, I'll make sure to direct everything in}
{17164}{}{the right way towards this goal. I will make them my}
{17165}{}{Horsemen of the Apocalypse, so even after I'm gone,}
{17166}{}{they'll wipe out all of humanity from this world.}
{17167}{}{**END-DISK**}

{18000}{}{Adviser Beldir Harding-Stillson.}
{18001}{}{Written on the occasion of emperor Myzrael's 60th}
{18002}{}{birthday - July 31 2167.}
{18003}{}{**END-PAR**}
{18004}{}{The history of the empire and its dwellers contains}
{18005}{}{many great stories that should never be forgotten.}
{18006}{}{Each affected the development of the monarchy, each}
{18007}{}{bears an important message. But three of these stories}
{18008}{}{stand out because their impact on the empire was}
{18009}{}{unmeasurable. In fact, the existence of the empire}
{18010}{}{would not be possible without them. That's why each of}
{18011}{}{us must take these three tales to heart, so that their}
{18012}{}{memory may be preserved forever.}
{18013}{}{**END-PAR**}
{18014}{}{**END-PAR**}
{18015}{}{The Schism at the Beginning of Life in Vault 16}
{18016}{}{When living on the surface became impossible, the}
{18017}{}{ancestors of today's imperial dwellers descended into a}
{18018}{}{vault numbered 16. That way, they saved themselves}
{18019}{}{from the radioactive fallout and were given the}
{18020}{}{opportunity to repopulate the Earth again in the}
{18021}{}{future. However, that hope could've been lost because}
{18022}{}{of a great dispute that erupted in the shelter. Because}
{18023}{}{of a gross administrative error, not one, but two}
{18024}{}{overseers were charged with the leadership of the}
{18025}{}{Vault. Elizabeth Stillson and Abraham Harding, a woman}
{18026}{}{and a man, both appointed to the same office. Each of}
{18027}{}{them supported by their subordinates and a large part}
{18028}{}{of ordinary people, neither willing to stand down.}
{18029}{}{Conflict seemed inevitable. But the overseers were wise}
{18030}{}{rulers and came up with a way to prevent unnecessary}
{18031}{}{bloodshed - they decided to appease the entire Vault by}
{18032}{}{marrying each other. That way they could both manage}
{18033}{}{the Vault. Both camps resisted their solution for a}
{18034}{}{while, but in the end, they recognized its wisdom.}
{18035}{}{During their wedding, they signed an agreement and}
{18036}{}{peace, welcomed with enthusiasm by everyone, had taken}
{18037}{}{hold in the Vault. That's how the united}
{18038}{}{Harding-Stillson family came to rule, consisting of}
{18039}{}{both first overseers and their closest relatives.}
{18040}{}{Together they looked after the welfare of the}
{18041}{}{community, and the burden of rule was subsequently}
{18042}{}{passed on to their descendants. This basic system has}
{18043}{}{lasted to the present day.}
{18044}{}{**END-PAR**}
{18045}{}{**END-PAR**}
{18046}{}{The Establishment of the Empire}
{18047}{}{After six decades spent in the Vault, the land became}
{18048}{}{habitable again, and Theodor, the overseer at the time}
{18049}{}{and the grandson of the first overseers, decided it was}
{18050}{}{time to resettle it. A difficult period of rebuilding}
{18051}{}{began, as the dwellers had to transform the ruins of}
{18052}{}{the old metropolis of Albuquerque into their new home.}
{18053}{}{Many demanding tasks awaited them. They learned the}
{18054}{}{practical use of old world technology, defended their}
{18055}{}{emerging city from enemy attacks, and made contacts}
{18056}{}{with the surrounding settlements. Overseer Theodor}
{18057}{}{wisely led them and always showed them the path they}
{18058}{}{needed to take. When eleven years had passed, he}
{18059}{}{considered his work complete and decided to pass the}
{18060}{}{rule to the people. However, they knew how much}
{18061}{}{Theodor did for them, and how important it was for him}
{18062}{}{to lead the City in the future as well. That's why they}
{18063}{}{declined his abdication. On the contrary, they came}
{18064}{}{with a proposal that would strengthen Theodor's}
{18065}{}{position even more. To show their appreciation for his}
{18066}{}{tremendous merits and to make sure the rule stays in}
{18067}{}{the hands of his descendants, they looked at the}
{18068}{}{examples from the old world, where they learned about}
{18069}{}{the title of emperor. Because the powers and majesty of}
{18070}{}{this position proved to be exactly what they wanted}
{18071}{}{for Theodor, they decided to award that title to him.}
{18072}{}{Internally, Theodor was against this, but he didn't}
{18073}{}{want to oppose the will of the people. That's why he}
{18074}{}{accepted the position. But he insisted that, at least,}
{18075}{}{a council with three members be created that would rule}
{18076}{}{together with him. That's how the empire and the}
{18077}{}{council of advisers were established. On the request of}
{18078}{}{the dwellers, only people from the Harding-Stillson}
{18079}{}{lineage are allowed to become advisers. And things have}
{18080}{}{remained that way until today.}
{18081}{}{**END-PAR**}
{18082}{}{**END-PAR**}
{18083}{}{The Great Ghoul Attack}
{18084}{}{Theodor died five years after the formation of the}
{18085}{}{empire, and was succeeded by his younger brother}
{18086}{}{Myzrael. Though he's as wise and capable as his}
{18087}{}{sibling, nothing could've prepared him for the what was}
{18088}{}{to come. During the second year of his rule, on the}
{18089}{}{night of February 6 2155, the empire was attacked by a}
{18090}{}{huge number of disciplined ghouls armed to the teeth,}
{18091}{}{bent on ransacking it completely. Despite the surprise}
{18092}{}{of their attack, the imperial army was able to quickly}
{18093}{}{organize itself and stop the ghoul onslaught. The}
{18094}{}{fierce battle lasted until dawn, and claimed many lives}
{18095}{}{of our best and most loyal troops. The ghouls were slow}
{18096}{}{to retreat at first, and tried several unsuccessful}
{18097}{}{counterattacks, but their retreat soon turned into a}
{18098}{}{cowardly escape and their army fell apart completely.}
{18099}{}{The imperial army was victorious. But because it lost}
{18100}{}{many men, and needed the rest for the direct defense of}
{18101}{}{the Imperial City, emperor Myzrael decided to negotiate}
{18102}{}{a contract with a faction called the Mutant Hunters. He}
{18103}{}{gave them the means to build their base in the vicinity}
{18104}{}{of the empire in return for a promise that they would}
{18105}{}{dispose of the ghoul threat. Originally, they asked for}
{18106}{}{much more in return for their services, from weapons to}
{18107}{}{the most advanced technologies of the City, but}
{18108}{}{Myzrael's deft negotiating prevented that. Sadly, the}
{18109}{}{Hunters are not too zealous in their task. During the}
{18110}{}{second ghoul attack seven years ago, they weren't even}
{18111}{}{able to keep their outer defensive positions and let}
{18112}{}{the enemy penetrate to the gates of the empire itself.}
{18113}{}{Thankfully, our soldiers demonstrated much greater}
{18114}{}{decisiveness and, at the cost of further casualties,}
{18115}{}{managed to stop the ghoul army again. Then, with}
{18116}{}{negligible help from the Hunters, they managed to turn}
{18117}{}{them back and force the ghouls to retreat. The empire}
{18118}{}{demonstrated its strength and the will to survive}
{18119}{}{again. There can be no doubt that a great future awaits}
{18120}{}{it under the wise rule of emperor Myzrael.}
{18121}{}{**END-DISK**}

{19000}{}{Written by colonel Parson. For emperor Aran's eyes}
{19001}{}{only.}
{19002}{}{**END-PAR**}
{19003}{}{With regards to the long-term loss of contact with the}
{19004}{}{second and third floors of Vault 16, as per given}
{19005}{}{order, I've created an operational group which was to}
{19006}{}{determine the status of the lost floors of the Vault}
{19007}{}{and prepare a plan to restore our control over them.}
{19008}{}{After seeing the image records from the lower floors,}
{19009}{}{which were recorded before the contact was interrupted,}
{19010}{}{I've deemed it necessary to get more information about}
{19011}{}{the situation in the Vault. Thus, I decided to form a}
{19012}{}{three-man reconnaissance team from the elite soldiers}
{19013}{}{of the empire - corporal Hicks and privates Hudson and}
{19014}{}{Vasquez. The team was instructed to inspect the status}
{19015}{}{of the lower floors of the Vault. Each member of the}
{19016}{}{team was equipped with the necessary technical}
{19017}{}{equipment to allow him to maintain radio and visual}
{19018}{}{contact during the mission. This allowed me to}
{19019}{}{simultaneously watch the entire operation and directly}
{19020}{}{intervene during the progress of the reconnaissance.}
{19021}{}{**END-PAR**}
{19022}{}{**END-PAR**}
{19023}{}{I've divided the progress of the reconnaissance mission}
{19024}{}{by time sequence for greater clarity:}
{19025}{}{**END-PAR**}
{19026}{}{6:30 - Start of the operation following the final}
{19027}{}{briefing. The team begins to descend to the second}
{19028}{}{floor.}
{19029}{}{**END-PAR**}
{19030}{}{6:34 - The team enters the second floor. The walls and}
{19031}{}{the floor are covered with a slimy matter of unknown}
{19032}{}{origin. The premises are visibly damaged, and most of}
{19033}{}{the devices do not work. I order the recon team to}
{19034}{}{scout the corridor and leisure quarters.}
{19035}{}{6:37 - An unidentified creature is spotted in the}
{19036}{}{resting area on the southwest of the floor. It is}
{19037}{}{approximately one meter tall and has dark purple skin}
{19038}{}{under a thin layer of slime. Judging by the upper limbs}
{19039}{}{- probably tentacles - and jaws, it is predatory. Its}
{19040}{}{appearance coincides with the profile of the creature}
{19041}{}{captured on record shortly before losing contact with}
{19042}{}{the lower floors. The creature registers corporal Hicks}
{19043}{}{and attacks him. The corporal starts firing on it but}
{19044}{}{the creature suffers no wounds from his light weapon.}
{19045}{}{It quickly, and with great agility, reaches the}
{19046}{}{corporal and kills him with its left tentacle. I order}
{19047}{}{Hudson and Vasquez to retreat immediately.}
{19048}{}{**END-PAR**}
{19049}{}{6:39 - The rest of the team manages to retreat into}
{19050}{}{the room across from the elevator without the predator}
{19051}{}{chasing them. After a brief radio communication, I}
{19052}{}{order them to head to the elevator and try to get into}
{19053}{}{the third floor. I task private Vasquez with attaching}
{19054}{}{the rope while private Hudson secures the corridor.}
{19055}{}{**END-PAR**}
{19056}{}{6:44 - Two more predators appear on the western end of}
{19057}{}{the corridor - one of them, judging by the slight}
{19058}{}{scratches on its body, is likely the attacker from the}
{19059}{}{previous encounter. Private Hudson initiates machine}
{19060}{}{gun fire and kills one of the creatures. However, the}
{19061}{}{second one manages to reach him and wrestles him to}
{19062}{}{the ground. At that moment, the video contact with him}
{19063}{}{is severed - private Hudson is most likely killed.}
{19064}{}{Private Vasquez manages to get to the elevator and go}
{19065}{}{down to the third floor.}
{19066}{}{**END-PAR**}
{19067}{}{6:47 - After private Vasquez descends, a shot is heard,}
{19068}{}{hitting him. He succumbs to his injuries almost}
{19069}{}{immediately. Before the connection is severed, it is}
{19070}{}{possible to see a defensive perimeter that was set up}
{19071}{}{there, as well as two armed men. Judging by their}
{19072}{}{equipment and badges, they were undoubtedly members}
{19073}{}{of the Mutant Hunters.}
{19074}{}{**END-PAR**}
{19075}{}{**END-PAR**}
{19076}{}{Despite the casualties, I deem the reconnaissance}
{19077}{}{mission to be a success. Due to the facts that were}
{19078}{}{discovered, our next course of action may only be}
{19079}{}{determined by direct orders from emperor Aran. End of}
{19080}{}{report.}
{19081}{}{**END-DISK**}

